              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " cascading gamma rays (1369- and 2754-keV) were",
                "detected by two Ge clover detectors.",
                "To stop the beta particles from reaching the germanium",
                "detectors, the carbon target and the two plastic",
                "detectors were surrounded by a box made with 2-mm-thick",
                "copper sheets. The detection system was shielded with",
                "7-cm-thick lead to reduce the cosmic ray background."
              ]
            }
